#SuperDays are days where you bring your best, be your best, be productive, have fun, and do what you would like to do and enjoy your little things your way. You lose sense of time in these days. You feel joy and satisfaction going back bed and it feels like you’ve done a lot and used your time well. A super day outweighs several days and maybe even several weeks. They highlight your week, or even your month or your whole year depending on how dead your routine is. 
Have more of these days. Spend time and money doing what feels right for YOU. Time does not stop and we’re not going back here. Enjoy your days people 🙌🏽

الجنون..جذور الكلمه مرتبطه بكلمة جنين وجن وهي اشياء خفية. الجنون هو عالم داخلي.. ممكن يكون فكر، حلم، فن، علم، طموح، او بكل بساطه طريقة منفرده لاستيعاب وترجمة العالم حولنا بغض النظر عن تصنيفها للصح او الخطأ. 
المجنون يتعمق في عالم داخلي مختلف عن المحيط الخارجي ويعيشه بتفرد. كلمة مجنون من الممكن انها تنطلق على مفكر او فنان او عالم او اي شخص يتعمق في عالمه الشخصي.. في طفولتنا كنا نعيش جنوننا ونبحر في عوالمنا الداخليه من دون اي حدود وقيود وهذا اللي يخلي عالم الطفوله ملون بآفاق غير محدوده.. انك تعيش جنونك الشخصي سواءا كان يناسب محيطك او لا هو المعنى الحقيقي للحريه وهو الطريق للابداع. 
خليك مجنون وعيش جنونك بطريقتك واحكامك لكن خليك مستعد انك تتحكم فيه وتتحرر منه وقت ماتحتاج.

Read this long post if you compete as a bodybuilder! 

We as bodybuilders often come from body insecurity background, inner demons, mental health issues, being bullied as kids, eating disorders etc. We find our niche in this “sport” if you wanna call it that. We fall in love with the journey of self improvement, building confidence, beating and taming ourselves, building discipline, and maybe finally expressing ourselves in public. Some want to deliver a message on stage, present an artwork if you look at it this way, or just simply putting our hard work into display.

What happens during the process is we become so fixated on bringing our best. We become so meticulous in our regimen. We get lost in the “whatever it takes” mentality and this sometimes can blind us from our initial goals. It can affect our personalities and reflect negatively on our immediate circle. We can become a burden to our loved ones. You will be more than lucky if your immediate circle fully understands what this all game means to you!

Now, while doing all this craziness, pay attention to your life! Health, time, and relationships. At the end of the day no one cares about it as you do! Take a moment to review your “why” and make sure you branch this out to other aspects of your life: being a good rule mode, having a sportsmanship, building discipline and being better every day outside of the gym, having balance in your life and most importantly having fun while doing what you love! 

I personally made a lot of mistakes when prepping for shows in the past. I pulled back and took a long break to reflect. Now I am so happy that I am finding balance and joy doing it in a better way with BALANCE. 
Nothing felt better than these moments when my kids were genuinely happy and excited for me. That was my win regardless of whatever place I would’ve gotten this last show ❤️

It’s always great to take a step back, reflect and reevaluate. We get one shot at this life and we should use our time wisely. Have a great Sunday everyone 🙌🏽

أي هدف في حياتك راح يتطلب منك تضحيات.. بعض هالتضحيات ممكن ماتقنع اللي حواليك وهذا مو مهم.. المهم انك انت مقتنع بها والأهم انها تكون في سبيل هدفك "أنت" مو هدف غيرك لو الشي اللي بيرضي غيرك.. اعطونا مافي جعبتكم سنة ٢٠٢٣ 😎

The journey is where the growth is.. The destination is just a dead end.. 

#practice #BetterThanYesterday

Gentle reminder for fellow bodybuilders:

You won’t be fully satisfied with your physique year round “especially if you compete and push limits” 

What you can do is try to be secure and happy with yourself year round.

Don’t get caught on the rat race of social media standards.. take the time to pull back and take care of your physical and mental wellbeing. #ComparisionIsTheThiefOfJoy

2019 ➡️ 2022
Embrace the journey, there are no destinations.. just stations that you need to experience 

#LiveitToTheFullest
#LiveYourObsession
